<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,<lb/>Bogotá</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-12"><hi rend="italic">September 12, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hart reports that it is probable the provisional government of the
                            Vice-President will be sustained; and that the Government announces that
                            the Liberal revolution is ended, only guerrillas remaining.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>